content: A wonderful digital version of one of the best 2 player card games. Knowing the rules of Morels helps a lot in this game. Playing with a friend is the way to go as their random matches can drag.

Fun game and decent adaptation. I like the sound effects, but not the background music, and selecting the cards one wants can be tricky on smaller screens. The AI opponents need to be revised -- I seldom lose against Easy, and rarely win against Medium.
So much fun! I really enjoy this game. Simple enough to understand quickly, but still complex enough to be super fun.
Love playing vs the "computer" but vs a randomly selected person is bad because there aren't enough people playing and they have 24 hours to make their move.
Excellent game! Very well put together, balanced.
Good version of the card game.
Fantastic two player
Fantastic way to practice strategy for playing the actual card game
Fun game. I love the card game version so I was excited for the app version
Please fix the multiplayer glitch
Please fix multiplayer not updating
Billy I find this an extremely entertaining game though it's very hard to play games with other people it also takes up a lot of space on your phone
Glitchy. Late game I can't cook mushrooms despite having a stack of frying pans. My gf and I love the game when it works but for $5 I want a playable game
This isn't allowing me to cook after a couple turns. I want my money back!!
Paid for foray and it's not working. Sometimes game freezes and you have to rotate screen or exit and enter to reload. Network play also sometimes need to reload to see if it's your turn.

Would be a 5 out of 5 except there is a glitch in multiplayer where towards the end of a game, turns will not update. I have to exit to the main menu and re enter the game in order for the turn to update. Very annoying and the glitch often only happens at the end of a game, but then will continue if I play another game immediately afterwards.
Are you ever going to fix the online multiplayer? You are charging people for a faulty product.
Good except multiplayer consistently requires app restart toward the end of a match to see other player's move.

Multiplayer is glitchy. My wife and I love the card game. We got the digital version to make setup easier. Unfortunately the Multiplayer is glitchy and multiple times per session turns do not update. You have to exit to the main menu and then re enter the game for it to update. Makes playing a very frustrating experience.

I purchased Foray to play the expanded game. It worked for a few days then asked me to pay $2.99 for the Foray expansion AGAIN. I was desperate to play with my wife so I even payed AGAIN and now it will not work. Please help.
Identical digital adaptation of a two player card game. Three difficulty levels. Two player mode plus online gaming option.

Super fun game. Bought it to play with friends online but the single player is fun too - just really hard to win against the computer. My only complaint is that while playing online the game often doesn't update automatically when your opponent makes move. So you have to keep exiting and entering the app to constantly reload it to check to see if the other player has taken their turn. This turns what would be a 5 min game into a 10 minute game with annoying procedures. Otherwise it's perfect.
Very good card game. Bought actual card game because I liked it so much
Love this game!
I really like it.
Great game!
Best two-player game since chess
Great game. However, I paid for the Foray expansion but I an unable to play a game with it; either against the AI or online.
Excellent adaption of a great game!
I own both versions of this game. Fun ouzzle to work out.
Love the game and that app has been excellent so far!
Very challenging and well put together
Really good port of an excellent two player card game.

This is both a solid game and a solid version of the physical card game. Such a strange game that is brutally addicting with excellent AI. I've been playing for weeks and still can't beat the Medium AI more often than losing. The only things this app could use is support for the optional circle layout for those of us that play the real game and support for more stats (win %, averages, etc). Both are minor.

This is a very well designed card game, based on collecting sets of mushrooms for cooking. Games are quick and quite challenging even with AI. Your strategy changes depending on the cards randomly available, which makes things more interesting. Graphics and ambient music are nice, and overall gameplay and mechanics are quite simple.
Expansion is not available when device is offline, which is a major deal breaker for me. Graphic design could use some work too - its not bad, but given how expensive the app is I would expect better
Absolutely love this game. Addictive and a robust app. I've already recommended it to friends! The Forays expansion is well worth the cash.
Great card-based game! I love it!
I love this game! Lots of fun to play alone or with friends. Beautiful art!
Wow! Great strategy game. Tough AI to beat. I'm not normally a board game fan, but this is an addicting and fun app. A keeper!
great game
Just like board game...love it
awesomeness

This game works correctly, so I am not faulting it at that. I may just not get this game, but I find nothing appealing about it other than the mushroom artwork. The random nature, fast moving resource row, and hand/action limitations do not work well in my mind. For what seems like a calming game, I have never found myself more aggravated. Maybe I need to read some strategy forum posts as I just don't see how this works at all.

Don't let the pricepoint put you off, this is basically a perfect, clean implementation of a great, simple game.  Tons of different playmodes available - though my preference is certainly for the base game. (Most play modes seem designed to make it more competitive / mathematics which is fair enough - but I'd be up for more goofy playstyles)

Simple but strategic Game that relies on looking ahead to see which cards are coming down the line and what sets your opponent is collecting. I enjoyed this little game which can be taught in 10 mins. If you like games like Jaipur and Lost cities, then add this to your collection.
Fun fungi game
Love this game and was pumped it was on mobile! plays well, the music is gorgeous. the computer is really challenging
Addictive, replayable, fun!
Really fun game. I'd like to see a resettable stats screen for win/loss count and ratio!
Great game! Wonderfully implemented and an addictive joy to play!

Brilliant 2 player strategic card game with a surprising amount of depth, and subtle tactics. The AI provides a challenging opponent, and the variations are welcome. Look forward to the expansion. Highly recommended.

Great for a solo game, against a very strong AI, but the online play essentially doesn't work. First, it gives 24 hours for each turn, which is excessive. Second, even if you try to start multiple games, it will keep matching you up with the same other (unresponsive) player. The interface is fairly good, but it is hard to see or follow what the other player has been doing.
The game is great, and the developers did a great job with the app. I'd gladly buy the Morels Foray expansion if it's ever available.
Wonderful implementation of a delightful card game.

When playing multiple games at once it would be great to be able to push an arrow or click a next button to go into the next game. Otherwise the game play and graphics are great and the game plays well on a phone.
Great game lots of fun to play with friends

This is a really good game with a neat theme and quick games. I'm bad at it and lose a lot but I find it a relaxing game. However it feels like there's not enough to it. I have heard there's an expansion for the physical tabletop Morels game, I hope we get that for this digital version also.
A faithful port of the great card game. Great game.
True to the board game. Very good. Well worth it in my opinion. If they end up adding the expansion even more so.
One of the best 2 player card games ever now with an excellent, smooth app.

Easy to learn and the game sessions go fast, so it's good for when you have just a few minutes waiting in line somewhere. I didn't mind the music and thought it was appropriate for a game set in the country.
Great digital implementation of the card game, really enjoying the game play.
Great implementation. Tutorial could use some tweaking for new players but gameplay is perfect.
